{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund a public health campaign to reduce the stigma of suicide",
        "additional_details": "Suicide is the biggest killer of young people, and is on the rise across the UK. Between 2012-2022, 73% of people who died by suicide were not mental health service patients, and we believe that stigma often stops people seeking help. A public health campaign could engage with suicide prevention charities and:\r\n\u2022 Normalise conversations about suicide\r\n\u2022 Increase public confidence in talking about suicidal thoughts\r\n\u2022 Encourage early help-seeking\r\n\u2022 Reduce shame and fear associated with suicidal feelings\r\n",
        "background": "Fund a multi-year campaign which should include mass media, social media, workplace toolkits, promotion in schools and universities, media collaboration and clear support signposting. Over five years, this should include development, pilots, evaluation and targeted campaigns for high risk groups.",
